- v1.7.0
    - **Write Buffer** ‚Äî in-process batch write optimization for high-frequency small upserts
        - New component: `WriteBufferManager` (`internal/buffer/write_buffer.go`)
            - Per-table channel + goroutine architecture (lazy-created per buffer key)
            - Flush triggers: batch full (2000 rows) / interval (configurable) / graceful shutdown
            - Bars + ext data bundled in single submission, flushed atomically
            - Non-blocking submit with 503 backpressure when channel full
        - `BarsController.Upsert()` routing logic:
            - `len(bars) >= direct_flush_threshold (500)` ‚Üí bypass buffer, direct DB write (full-load path)
            - `len(bars) < 500` ‚Üí submit to write buffer (daily-update path)
        - New endpoint: `GET /api/v2/buffer/stats` ‚Äî per-buffer metrics (submitted/flushed/pending/flush_count)
        - New biz_config section: `write_buffer` (enabled, max_batch_size, flush_interval, direct_flush_threshold, channel_size, shutdown_timeout)
        - New `internal/config/config.go` ‚Äî PhoenixA BizConfig + `SetBizConfig` init
        - Unit tests: 6 test cases covering disabled/interval-flush/batch-full/channel-full/ext-bundled/multi-key
        - Design doc: `docs/2026-05-07 DESIGN_BATCH_WRITE_BUFFER.md`
- v1.6.0
    - **PostgreSQL Migration Phase 2** ‚Äî financial_statement & corporate_action tables migrated to PostgreSQL
        - `FinancialStatementDao` and `CorporateActionDao` switched from `mysql_gorm` to `postgres_gorm`
        - `SchemaDao` switched to `postgres_gorm`; JSON queries rewritten: `JSON_TABLE`/`JSON_KEYS` ‚Üí `LATERAL jsonb_object_keys()`
        - New PostgreSQL migration: `migrations/postgresql/security/0002_financial_data.sql`
            - 2 tables: `financial_statement`, `corporate_action` with PG-native types
            - JSONB GIN indexes (`jsonb_path_ops`): `idx_fs_data_gin`, `idx_ca_data_gin`
            - Partial indexes on `ann_date` and `comp_type_code`
        - **JSONB query capabilities**:
            - `FinancialStatementFilters` / `CorporateActionFilters`: new `DataContains` (`@>`) and `DataHasKey` (`?`) fields
            - Enables queries like: `WHERE data_json @> '{"TOTAL_ASSETS": 100000000}'`
        - Model updates: `type:json` ‚Üí `type:jsonb`, `int` ‚Üí `smallint` for `comp_type_code`
        - Bug fix: `_int()` in Artemis `base_financial_statement.py` ‚Äî `int(float(val))` for `COMP_TYPE_CODE` type inconsistency
        - New doc: `2026-05-07 FINANCIAL_DATA_PG_MIGRATION.md`
        - Upgrade infra to v0.17.2 to support latest `postgres_gorm` features.
- v1.5.0
    - **PostgreSQL Migration Phase 1** ‚Äî taxonomy & industry tables migrated to PostgreSQL
        - **Only TaxonomyDao** switched from `mysql_gorm` to `postgres_gorm`
        - All other DAOs (security, bars, strategy_run, financial_statement, corporate_action, schema) remain on MySQL
        - New PostgreSQL migration: `migrations/postgresql/security/0001_security_init.sql`
            - 5 tables: taxonomy_category, taxonomy_security_map, industry_constituent, industry_weight, industry_daily
            - PG-native types: BIGSERIAL, BOOLEAN, JSONB, TIMESTAMPTZ, NUMERIC
        - **JSONB advantages leveraged**:
            - `taxonomy_category.attrs_json` uses JSONB with GIN index (`idx_tc_attrs_gin`)
            - Enables fast `@>` containment queries: e.g. `WHERE attrs_json @> '{"is_pub": 1}'`
            - Enables `?` key-existence queries: e.g. `WHERE attrs_json ? 'change_reason'`
            - `TaxonomyCategoryFilters` gains `AttrsContains` and `AttrsHasKey` fields
        - `config.yaml`: added `postgres_gorm.data_sources.security` (schema: `security_dev`)
        - `mysql_gorm` kept enabled ‚Äî all non-taxonomy DAOs still read/write MySQL
        - Taxonomy model updated: `tinyint unsigned` ‚Üí `smallint`, `tinyint(1)` ‚Üí `boolean`, `json` ‚Üí `jsonb`
